<HtmlPage title="Home">
  <HomeLayout>

    <hr>

      <p>Oh hi ! Welcome to the home page of my website !</p>
      <p>I did debate with myself for quite some time on whether this should be the "Home" or "Hub" page, which would functionally be the same, so I guess I can always change it later. </p>
      <p>We really need to invent new words. </p>

    <hr>

      <p>Anyways, ... Oh right, my name ! My legal name is Yann, although I find it doesn't sound amazing in an english sentence, and my online name attached to my real life identity is Green Jacket Boy, or Green for short.</p>
      <p>As an alternative you can call me Glenn, it's a good balance between my legal and online name, and it doesn't sound strange in an english sentence. I also happen to really like this name.</p>

    <hr>

    <h1>Train Station :</h1>

      <div class="train-station-element">
        <h2><a href="/Portfolio">Portfolio</a></h2>
        <p>Written in french (faq : <a href="QA#whats-up-with-all-the-languages">What's with  the languages ?</a>), it is a aimed at companies and recruiters, you can see it as my resume, but with a lot more content, details and personal touch.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="train-station-element">
        <h2><a href="/Articles">Personal Blog</a></h2>
        <p>A place for me to write articles about pretty much anything, including but not limited to Science, Technology, Programming and Video Games.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="train-station-element">
        <h2><a href="/QA">Q&A</a></h2>
        <p>Answers to questions you might (or most probably might not) have about me and this website.</p>
      </div>

    <hr>

    <h1 id="Contact">Contact :</h1>

      <p>If you wish to contact me, you can do so by sending me an email at <b>greenjacketboy&#64;proton.me</b>, or by writing me a message on <b><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/green-jacket/" target="_blank">Linkedin</a></b>.</p>
      <p>It's worth noting that this is not <i>really</i> my professional email. Just like my phone number I would prefer not to have it publicly on the internet. Of course it doesn't mean that you can't contact me for professional reasons through this email. </p>
  </HomeLayout>
</HtmlPage>

